{
  "stem": "14900.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "The ride wasn't quite as long-- maybe two-- two days and a night or two nights.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "We were marched in the middle of the night, pouring mud.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And I tripped on something, twisted my ankle, and something lodged in my ankle-- very deep.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "I didn't dare even falter.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "I kept limping but going.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "I had to keep up the pace.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "When we got into the cattle car for that, I was ready to pass out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "One of my friends held my leg, another one-- and they let me spread it across them-- with all her might, pulled this thing out.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "And it was a rusty, one-inch-long screw.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "It was quite thick.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "I had a scar for years.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "I still have a dimple there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "When the other people on the train realized that I was injured-- and my leg, of course, was throbbing, swelling, pussy-- they proceeded to kick it and hit it-- so that we were all becoming animals-- so that I'd pull it back and they'd have the space.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "Well, we did arrive in Magdeburg.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "My ankle was about triple its size, full of pus.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "We were marched to our barracks in the labor camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "It was a room with windows; triple bunks, but space on it; clean straw.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "And it was actually warm compared to what we were used to-- still freezing cold, but at least the wind didn't howl through it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "And on the next day, a woman-- a tall, austere-looking German female-- came to select for whatever it was she was selecting for.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "And she picked 10 of us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "And we all noticed the same thing and were terrified.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 77,
      "text": "We were the smallest, the scrawniest, the sickest-looking in the group.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 78,
      "text": "And she marched us at full pace to work.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
